   "source": [
    "# StoryForge AI вЂ” ShopFlow POC\n",
    "\n",
    "> *From a plain English user story to executable test scripts вЂ” fully on-premise, zero data egress.*\n",
     > **Note:** This notebook demonstrates the pipeline architecture in simulated mode. For live Mistral 7B output run: `python3 generate.py --story US-001`
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## User Story вЂ” US-001\n",
    "\n",
    "**As a registered shopper on ShopFlow**, I want to search for a product, add it to my cart, and complete payment so that my **order is placed** and I receive an **order confirmation with a unique order ID**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Pipeline Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "| Stage | Description | Output |\n",
    "|-------|-------------|--------|\n",
    "| 1 | **Dependencies** вЂ” verify all libraries installed | вњ… Confirmed |\n",
    "| 2 | **Configuration** вЂ” load YAML config files | Config summary |\n",
    "| 3 | **Parsing Engine** вЂ” extract AC from user story | ParsedSpec JSON |\n",
    "| 4 | **Test Case Generator** вЂ” generate 18 test cases | Test Case tables |\n",
    "| 5 | **Test Data Generator** вЂ” Faker seed=42 | test_data.json |\n",
    "| 6 | **Coverage Report** вЂ” map tests to AC | PASS / FAIL verdict |\n",
    "| 7 | **Code Synthesis** вЂ” Jinja2 renders scripts | .java / .spec.ts files |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8988f17e-b983-4a33-b254-5d9242343a9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
